{#incident}
@summary: Incident response timeline template
# Incident Timeline

- T+00m: Detect alert and declare incident
- T+05m: Assign incident commander and scribe
- T+15m: Share initial customer update
- T+30m: Identify mitigation steps

Keep all timestamps in UTC and link the primary ticket.
If mitigation requires reversal, follow {@rollback}.
After stabilization, capture outcomes in {@postmortem}.
{/incident}

{#rollback}
@summary: Rollback steps with commands
# Rollback Steps

1. Pause deploys for the affected service
2. Roll back to the last known good release
3. Validate service health

```
./deploy freeze
./deploy rollback --service api --to release-2025-01-18
./deploy status --service api
```

After service recovery, complete the {@postmortem} checklist.
{/rollback}

